# Prefer modern CLI tools

When you suggest or run shell commands (e.g. search, list files, view diffs, run scripts), prefer these tools:

| Avoid              | Prefer                             | Use for                                    |
| ------------------ | ---------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| `grep`             | `rg` (ripgrep)                     | Content search (fast, respects .gitignore) |
| `find`             | `fd`                               | File discovery (simpler syntax)            |
| `cat`              | `bat`                              | Viewing files (syntax highlighting)        |
| `ls`               | `eza`                              | Listing directories (icons, git status)    |
| `git diff` (plain) | `git diff` with **delta** as pager | Readable diffs (if delta is configured)    |
| asdf / nvm / pyenv | **mise**                           | Version management (Node, Python, etc.)    |

